contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox protected area of Australia | name = Gundabooka National Park | iucn_category = II | image = | caption = | map = | map_caption = | locator_x = | locator_y = | location = | nearest_town_or_city= [[Bourke, New South Wales|Bourke]] | coordinates = {{Coord|30|30|10|S|145|42|50|E|type:landmark_region:AU-NSW|display=inline,title}} | area = | established = 1996 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | managing_authorities = [[National Parks and Wildlife Service (New South Wales)|NSW National Parks and Wildlife Service]] | official_site = http://www.nationalparks.nsw.gov.au }} '''Gundabooka''' is a [[national park]] in [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]]. The park is located 70 km south of [[Bourke, New South Wales|Bourke]], Australia. [[Mount Gunderbooka]] (as spelt) is located within the park. Prior to becoming a park the area was home to the [[Ngemba]] and a sheep [[Station (Australian agriculture)|station]]. [[Petroglyph]] rock art and ancestral ceremonial grounds are located inside the park. It has many exotic plants. ==See also== * [[Protected areas of New South Wales]] {{National Parks of New South Wales}} [[Category:National parks of New South Wales]] [[Category:1996 establishments in Australia]] {{NewSouthWales-protected-area-stub}}
